        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         As I mentioned to you in IRC today I have been running these tests already and plan upon doing some more extensive testing this weekend.  So far I have tested EoT and Servant of Bones using Augmentation of Death and Augement Death.</P><P>So far there has been very little difference in their damage output between the two haste buffs.  Going to do some more test this weekend to get a better test bed but I believe that Mages are correct and pets are currently limited to a 60% haste buff.  Not a huge deal for Necromancers (as our top haste buff is 65%) but this reall sucks for Mages and Beastlords (BLs have an 85% pet haste buff).</P><P>Will post some information later this weekend.  If anyone else wants to do these test please use a soulbinder as the target.  This has been the test mob that all the Mage and BL haste tests have been performed upon, so we should use the same for consistancy.</P><P>Bril</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
